      <originalsloc id="aspace_65f3fddb3cfafef809cddcafc5cb9fc5">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>The entire collection can be located in the Account Books Collection (MS 29).   The collection is an artificial collection of account books and financial volumes, ca. 1680-1930, relating to such occupations as: farmers, merchants, traders, millers, blacksmiths, lawyers, manufacturers, laborers, physicians, shoemakers, carpenters, tailors, and cigar makers. Materials relating to private organizations and businesses are also included. The collection focuses on the Connecticut and New England region.</p>
         <p>HM 244 only consists of an account book from New Haven, Connecticut, ca. 1695-1850</p>  
